Note: ================================================================
Note: Bifrost OpenCL Backend
Note: ================================================================
Note: Generates OpenCL C code from Bifrost IR for cross-platform GPUs.
Note: Supports OpenCL 1.2/2.0/3.0 features: kernels, local memory,
Note: work-group operations, atomic operations, and vendor extensions.
Note: ================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/bifrost/graph/graph.runa" as Graph
Import "compiler/middle/bifrost/graph/node.runa" as Node
Import "compiler/middle/bifrost/graph/edge.runa" as Edge
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringMod
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/emitter_common.runa" as Emitter
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/arithmetic_core.runa" as Math

Note: ================================================================
Note: OpenCL Address Space Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant OPENCL_GLOBAL as Integer is 0     Note: __global memory (device DRAM)
Constant OPENCL_LOCAL as Integer is 1      Note: __local memory (on-chip shared)
Constant OPENCL_CONSTANT as Integer is 2   Note: __constant memory (cached, read-only)
Constant OPENCL_PRIVATE as Integer is 3    Note: __private memory (registers)

Note: ================================================================
Note: OpenCL Version Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant OPENCL_1_2 as Integer is 120
Constant OPENCL_2_0 as Integer is 200
Constant OPENCL_3_0 as Integer is 300

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Definitions
Note: ================================================================

Type called "OpenCLKernel":
    name as String                  Note: Kernel function name
    parameters as Integer           Note: List of OpenCLParameter
    body as String                  Note: Kernel body code
    local_memory_bytes as Integer   Note: Local memory requirement
    work_group_size as Integer      Note: Work-group size (threads per group)
    preferred_multiple as Integer   Note: Preferred work-group size multiple
End Type

Type called "OpenCLParameter":
    name as String                  Note: Parameter name
    opencl_type as String           Note: OpenCL type (float*, int, etc.)
    address_space as Integer        Note: OPENCL_* address space
    is_const as Boolean             Note: Whether parameter is const
End Type

Type called "OpenCLDevice":
    platform_id as Integer          Note: Platform identifier
    device_id as Integer            Note: Device identifier
    device_type as Integer          Note: GPU, CPU, ACCELERATOR
    max_compute_units as Integer    Note: Number of compute units
    max_work_group_size as Integer  Note: Maximum work-group size
End Type

Note: ================================================================
Note: Code Generation - Top Level
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
generate_opencl_code is the top-level entry point that lowers a Bifrost
graph to a complete OpenCL C source string. The output is structured into
pragmas, extensions, typedefs, kernel function, and host setup comments so
the result can be cleanly partitioned by callers. Traversal is in
topological order so operations are emitted with all operands already
declared.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Creates an empty StringMod buffer. Appends in order:
1. Pragmas via generate_opencl_pragmas(opencl_version).
2. Extensions via generate_opencl_extensions(opencl_version).
3. Type definitions via generate_type_definitions(graph).
4. The kernel function via generate_kernel_function(graph, kernel_name,
   opencl_version).
5. Host-side setup comments via generate_host_setup_comments(graph,
   kernel_name).
Each section is separated by "\n\n". Returns the buffer converted to
String via StringMod.to_string.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(V+E) where V and E are the graph's node and edge counts. Dominated by
generate_kernel_function. String concatenation is amortised by the
StringMod buffer.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation; reads the graph and produces a fresh String owned by
caller. No syscalls, no host execution - this routine emits source code,
not running compute.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_opencl_code" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    Let opencl_code be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    Note: Add OpenCL version pragma
    Let pragmas be generate_opencl_pragmas(opencl_version)
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, pragmas
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Add extension declarations
    Let extensions be generate_opencl_extensions(opencl_version)
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, extensions
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Add type definitions
    Let typedefs be generate_type_definitions(graph)
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, typedefs
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Generate kernel function
    Let kernel be generate_kernel_function(graph, kernel_name, opencl_version)
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, kernel
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Generate host-side setup documentation
    Let setup be generate_host_setup_comments(graph, kernel_name)
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with opencl_code, setup

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with opencl_code
End Process

@Reasoning
generate_opencl_pragmas emits the #pragma OPENCL EXTENSION directives
needed by the kernel. Version 2.0+ also enables int64 atomics. fp64 is
emitted for all versions because Bifrost typically uses double precision.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a fresh StringMod buffer. If opencl_version >= OPENCL_2_0,
appends three pragmas (cl_khr_fp64, cl_khr_int64_base_atomics,
cl_khr_int64_extended_atomics). Otherwise appends only cl_khr_fp64.
Converts the buffer to String and returns it.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - a small constant number of string appends.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation. Output is a String owned by caller.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_opencl_pragmas" that takes opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    Let pragmas be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    If opencl_version is greater than or equal to OPENCL_2_0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_fp64 : enable\n"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_int64_base_atomics : enable\n"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_int64_extended_atomics : enable\n"
    Otherwise:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_fp64 : enable\n"
    End If

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with pragmas
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits OpenCL-version-conditional comments documenting which feature set the
kernel is targeting (SVM and generic address space at 2.0+, compatibility
mode at 1.2).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Creates an empty StringMod buffer. Appends a generic header comment, then a
version-specific comment line (2.0+ vs 1.2). Returns the StringMod buffer
as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_opencl_extensions" that takes opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    Let extensions be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with extensions, "// OpenCL extensions for enhanced functionality\n"

    If opencl_version is greater than or equal to OPENCL_2_0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with extensions, "// OpenCL 2.0+ features: SVM, generic address space, work-group functions\n"
    Otherwise:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with extensions, "// OpenCL 1.2 compatibility mode\n"
    End If

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with extensions
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits OpenCL C typedef aliases (uchar, ushort, uint, ulong) so the rest of
the generated code can use these names without relying on the host
toolchain's typedefs. These names map 1:1 to OpenCL built-in types and are
consistent across NVIDIA, AMD, and Intel implementations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends a comment header followed by four
typedef declarations (uchar, ushort, uint, ulong). Returns the buffer as a
String. The graph parameter is reserved for future per-graph type
specialisation.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - four string appends.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_type_definitions" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let typedefs be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    Note: Add common type aliases
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with typedefs, "// Type definitions\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with typedefs, "typedef unsigned char uchar;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with typedefs, "typedef unsigned short ushort;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with typedefs, "typedef unsigned int uint;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with typedefs, "typedef unsigned long ulong;\n"

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with typedefs
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Kernel Generation
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
generate_kernel_function emits the actual OpenCL __kernel definition: the
signature with address-space-qualified parameters (__global, __local),
work-item index computation, local memory declarations, the body lowered
from the graph, and a final barrier. Combining these into a single producer
keeps the kernel structure consistent across graphs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a kernel_code StringMod buffer. Appends "__kernel void " plus
kernel_name, then calls generate_kernel_parameters to fill the parameter
list, generate_work_item_index_computation for the get_global_id setup,
generate_local_memory_declarations for any __local buffers, and
generate_kernel_body for the actual operation emission. Wraps everything
in the function body. Returns the kernel as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(V+E) where V and E are the graph sizes. Dominated by the inner body
emission.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation. The output is a String owned by caller; no syscalls.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_kernel_function" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    Let kernel_code be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    Note: Generate kernel signature
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, "__kernel void "
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, kernel_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, "(\n"

    Note: Generate parameters
    Let params be generate_kernel_parameters(graph)
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, params
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, "\n {\n"

    Note: Generate work-item index computation
    Let work_item_idx be generate_work_item_index_computation()
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, work_item_idx

    Note: Generate local memory declarations
    Let local_mem be generate_local_memory_declarations(graph)
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, local_mem

    Note: Generate kernel body
    Let body be generate_kernel_body(graph, opencl_version)
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, body

    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with kernel_code, "}\n"

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with kernel_code
End Process

@Reasoning
generate_kernel_parameters scans the graph's Input and Output nodes and
emits an OpenCL parameter list with the correct address-space qualifiers
(__global for buffers, __local for shared memory, scalar for size). The
order matches the host-side launch convention so the host does not need
extra binding logic.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer. Walks Graph.get_all_nodes and emits, for each
Input node (NodeType 1), a "__global const TYPE* input_i" parameter, and
for each Output node (NodeType 2), a "__global TYPE* output_i" parameter.
After all I/O nodes, appends "__local float* local_mem" and "int size" as
the trailing parameters. Commas and newlines separate parameters.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(N) where N is graph node count - one pass over Graph.get_all_nodes plus
constant trailing parameters.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation; emits a String with the parameter list.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_kernel_parameters" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let params be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    Note: Get input and output nodes
    Let all_nodes be proc get_all_nodes from Graph with graph
    Let param_count be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than proc length from List with all_nodes:
        Let node be proc get from List with all_nodes, i
        Let node_type be proc get_node_type from Node with node

        Note: NodeType: Input=1, Output=2
        If node_type is equal to 1:
            Note: Input parameter
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, ",\n"
            End If

            Let opencl_type be map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(proc get_node_output_type from Node with node)
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, "    __global const "
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, opencl_type
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, "* input_"
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, StringPrim.integer_to_string(i )

            Set param_count to param_count plus 1
        End If

        If node_type is equal to 2:
            Note: Output parameter
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, ",\n"
            End If

            Set opencl_type to map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(proc get_node_output_type from Node with node)
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, "    __global "
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, opencl_type
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, "* output_"
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, StringPrim.integer_to_string(i )

            Set param_count to param_count plus 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add local memory parameter
    If param_count is greater than 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, ",\n"
    End If
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, "    __local float* local_mem"
    Set param_count to param_count plus 1

    Note: Add size parameter
    If param_count is greater than 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, ",\n"
    End If
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with params, "    int size"

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with params
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits OpenCL's standard work-item index preamble (get_global_id,
get_local_id, get_group_id) plus the gid-bounds-check that prevents
out-of-range work-items from executing kernel body. This pattern is
recognised by every OpenCL implementation as the canonical setup.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer. Appends a comment header followed by four C
statements: "int gid = get_global_id(0);", "int lid = get_local_id(0);",
"int group_id = get_group_id(0);", and "if (gid >= size) return;".
Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - constant number of string appends.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_work_item_index_computation" that takes nothing returns String:
    Let code be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    // Compute global work-item index\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    int gid = get_global_id(0 ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    int lid = get_local_id(0 ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    int group_id = get_group_id(0 ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    if (gid >= size return;\n\n"

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with code
End Process

@Reasoning
Local memory in OpenCL is on-chip per-compute-unit storage shared by all
work-items in a work-group. Today it is passed in via the kernel parameter
local_mem rather than declared inline; this routine emits a documentation
comment so the generated kernel makes the intent visible.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends two comment lines noting that
local memory is available via the kernel parameter and the typical size
budget (1024 bytes for 256 floats). Returns the buffer as a String. The
graph parameter is reserved for future per-graph local-memory budget
analysis.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_local_memory_declarations" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    // Local memory available via kernel parameter\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    // Typical size: 256 floats = 1024 bytes\n\n"

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with code
End Process

@Reasoning
generate_kernel_body lowers the graph's operation nodes to OpenCL C
statements in topological order, recording per-node output variable names
in a Dict so emit_operation_code can resolve operand references on later
nodes. Topological order guarantees every operand has been emitted before
its consumer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a body StringMod buffer. Runs Graph.topological_sort to get the
node order. Creates a var_names Dict for SSA-to-C-variable mapping. Walks
the sorted node list and calls emit_operation_code(node, var_names, i,
opencl_version) for each node, appending the returned code into the body
buffer. Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(V) topological sort plus O(per-node) emission cost. The total kernel
body is linear in graph size.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation; allocates and owns one Dict and one StringMod
buffer. No external state.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_kernel_body" that takes graph as Integer, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    Let body be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    Note: Get topological sort
    Let sorted_nodes be proc topological_sort from Graph with graph

    Note: Track variable names
    Let var_names be proc create from Dict

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than proc length from List with sorted_nodes:
        Let node be proc get from List with sorted_nodes, i

        Note: Generate code for this operation
        Let op_code be emit_operation_code(node, var_names, i, opencl_version)
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with body, op_code

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with body
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Operation Code Emission
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
emit_operation_code is the dispatcher that maps Bifrost OpKind discriminants
to concrete OpenCL C expressions. Each variant produces a typed declaration
of var_i and assigns the appropriate expression (arithmetic, activation,
intrinsic). Variable naming is index-based to keep symbols collision-free
across kernels.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a code StringMod buffer. Reads the node's OpKind. Builds a
result_var_name as "var_" + index and registers (node -> name) in
var_names. Maps the node's output type to its OpenCL C type. Then
dispatches by op_kind: 0-4 emit binary arithmetic (Add/Sub/Mul/Div/Mod);
20-22 emit activation functions (ReLU as max(0.0f, x), Sigmoid as 1.0/(1.0+exp(-x)),
Tanh via tanh()); 30-32 emit math intrinsics (Exp/Log/Sqrt). Each variant
fetches operand variable names via get_input_variable and writes the
C-style declaration to the code buffer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) per node - one Dict insert plus a fixed number of string appends per
opcode. The full dispatch table is a linear If-cascade but bounded to ~50
opcodes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Mutates the caller-owned var_names Dict. Returns a freshly allocated String.
Pure code generation; no syscalls.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "emit_operation_code" that takes node as Integer, var_names as Integer, index as Integer, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    Let op_kind be proc get_node_opkind from Node with node

    Note: Get result variable name
    Let result_var be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with result_var, "var_"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with result_var, StringPrim.integer_to_string(index )
    Let result_var_name be proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with result_var

    Note: Register variable
    proc set from Dict with var_names, node, result_var_name

    Note: Get OpenCL type
    Let output_type be proc get_node_output_type from Node with node
    Let opencl_type be map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(output_type)

    Note: Emit operation based on OpKind
    Note: Add=0, Subtract=1, Multiply=2, Divide=3
    If op_kind is equal to 0:
        Note: Add operation
        Let inputs be proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, opencl_type
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, result_var_name
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " = "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input1_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " + "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input2_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, ";\n"

        Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with code
    End If

    If op_kind is equal to 1:
        Note: Subtract operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, opencl_type
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, result_var_name
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " = "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input1_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " - "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input2_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, ";\n"

        Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with code
    End If

    If op_kind is equal to 2:
        Note: Multiply operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, opencl_type
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, result_var_name
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " = "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input1_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " * "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input2_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, ";\n"

        Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with code
    End If

    If op_kind is equal to 3:
        Note: Divide operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, opencl_type
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, result_var_name
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " = "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input1_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " / "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input2_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, ";\n"

        Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with code
    End If

    Note: Modulo=4
    If op_kind is equal to 4:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, opencl_type
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, result_var_name
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " = "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input1_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " % "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input2_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, ";\n"

        Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with code
    End If

    Note: ReLU=20
    If op_kind is equal to 20:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "    "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, opencl_type
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, result_var_name
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " = max(0.0f, "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, input_var
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, " ;\n"

