Note: ================================================================
Note: Host-Side Setup Documentation
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
Embeds a complete OpenCL host-side setup recipe (9 stages from platform
selection through resource cleanup) as a C-style comment block in the
emitted kernel source. Putting the recipe next to the kernel keeps
host-side launch code discoverable by anyone reading the generated source.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends a C-style block comment ("/* ...
*/") that walks the OpenCL API call sequence: clGetPlatformIDs ->
clGetDeviceIDs -> clCreateContext -> clCreateCommandQueue ->
clCreateProgramWithSource -> clBuildProgram -> clCreateKernel (with
kernel_name interpolated) -> clCreateBuffer (input/output/local) ->
clEnqueueWriteBuffer -> clSetKernelArg (four args) -> clEnqueueNDRangeKernel
-> clEnqueueReadBuffer -> clRelease* cleanup. Returns the buffer as a
String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - constant number of string appends, regardless of graph size. The
emitted comment is a fixed template.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation. The graph parameter is unused today but reserved
for per-graph customisation (e.g. emitting per-buffer sizes).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_host_setup_comments" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    Let comments be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, "/*\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * Host-side OpenCL setup (C/C++ :\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 1. Get platform and device:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_platform_id platform;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clGetPlatformIDs(1, &platform, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_device_id device;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clGetDeviceIDs(platform, CL_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU, 1, &device, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 2. Create context and command queue:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_context context = clCreateContext(NULL, 1, &device, NULL, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_command_queue queue = clCreateCommandQueue(context, device, 0, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 3. Compile kernel:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_program program = clCreateProgramWithSource(context, 1, &kernelSource, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clBuildProgram(program, 1, &device, NULL, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_kernel kernel = clCreateKernel(program, \""
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, kernel_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, "\", NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 4. Create buffers:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_mem inputBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_READ_ONLY, dataSize, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_mem outputBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_WRITE_ONLY, dataSize, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    cl_mem localBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_READ_WRITE, localSize, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 5. Copy data to device:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clEnqueueWriteBuffer(queue, inputBuffer, CL_TRUE, 0, dataSize, hostInput, 0, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 6. Set kernel arguments:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 0, sizeof(cl_mem , &inputBuffer);\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 1, sizeof(cl_mem , &outputBuffer);\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 2, 256 * sizeof(float , NULL); // Local memory\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 3, sizeof(int , &size);\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 7. Execute kernel:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    size_t globalSize = (size + 255 / 256 * 256;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    size_t localSize = 256;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clEnqueueNDRangeKernel(queue, kernel, 1, NULL, &globalSize, &localSize, 0, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 8. Read results:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clEnqueueReadBuffer(queue, outputBuffer, CL_TRUE, 0, dataSize, hostOutput, 0, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " * 9. Cleanup:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clReleaseMemObject(inputBuffer ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clReleaseMemObject(outputBuffer ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clReleaseKernel(kernel ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clReleaseProgram(program ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clReleaseCommandQueue(queue ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " *    clReleaseContext(context ;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with comments, " */\n"

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with comments
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Mapping
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
Maps a Bifrost type pointer to the OpenCL C type name used in kernel
declarations. Primitives map to char / short / int / long / float / double
based on the primitive kind; Vector types translate to OpenCL's
SoA-style float2/float4/float8/float16 vector tags when the lane count
matches, otherwise to pointer types; Matrix and Tensor lower to float*
because OpenCL has no first-class matrix type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns "void" if bifrost_type is 0. Reads the discriminant. For Primitive
(0) reads prim_kind and returns char/short/int/long/float/double via
direct comparisons, falling back to "int" on unknown. For Vector (2) reads
element_type and lane count, calls map_primitive_to_opencl on the element,
and concatenates "2"/"3"/"4"/"8"/"16" for the known lane widths or appends
"*" for unsupported widths. Matrix (3) and Tensor (5) both return
"float*". Unknown discriminants return "float".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - a bounded If-cascade plus at most one string concatenation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read; returns interned string literals or freshly concatenated
strings owned by caller.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "map_bifrost_type_to_opencl" that takes bifrost_type as Integer returns String:
    If bifrost_type is equal to 0:
        Return "void"
    End If

    Let discriminant be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 0

    Note: Primitive types
    If discriminant is equal to 0:
        Let prim_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 8

        Note: INT8=0, INT16=1, INT32=2, INT64=3
        If prim_kind is equal to 0:
            Return "char"
        End If
        If prim_kind is equal to 1:
            Return "short"
        End If
        If prim_kind is equal to 2:
            Return "int"
        End If
        If prim_kind is equal to 3:
            Return "long"
        End If

        Note: FLOAT32=6, FLOAT64=7
        If prim_kind is equal to 6:
            Return "float"
        End If
        If prim_kind is equal to 7:
            Return "double"
        End If

        Return "int"
    End If

    Note: Vector types
    If discriminant is equal to 2:
        Let element_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 8
        Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 16

        Note: OpenCL vector types: float2, float4, float8, float16
        Let elem_opencl be map_primitive_to_opencl(element_type)

        If size is equal to 2:
            Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with elem_opencl, "2"
        End If
        If size is equal to 3:
            Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with elem_opencl, "3"
        End If
        If size is equal to 4:
            Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with elem_opencl, "4"
        End If
        If size is equal to 8:
            Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with elem_opencl, "8"
        End If
        If size is equal to 16:
            Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with elem_opencl, "16"
        End If

        Note: Other sizes use pointers
        Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with elem_opencl, "*"
    End If

    Note: Matrix and Tensor types use pointers
    If discriminant is equal to 3:
        Return "float*"
    End If
    If discriminant is equal to 5:
        Return "float*"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper for map_bifrost_type_to_opencl that turns a raw primitive kind code
into the OpenCL C scalar type name. Kept separate so Vector lowering can
call it without re-implementing the cascade.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns "char" for kind 0 (INT8), "int" for kind 2 (INT32), "float" for
kind 6 (FLOAT32), "double" for kind 7 (FLOAT64). Returns "float" as the
safe fallback for any other kind code (intentionally narrower than
map_bifrost_type_to_opencl which handles short/long; this helper is
optimised for the vector-component path where float dominates).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - up to four compares.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read; returns interned string literals.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "map_primitive_to_opencl" that takes prim_kind as Integer returns String:
    If prim_kind is equal to 0:
        Return "char"
    End If
    If prim_kind is equal to 2:
        Return "int"
    End If
    If prim_kind is equal to 6:
        Return "float"
    End If
    If prim_kind is equal to 7:
        Return "double"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
Resolves an operand reference during emit_operation_code to its OpenCL C
variable name. Graph inputs (no var_names entry) return the canonical
"input_0[gid]" indexed-buffer access; intermediate values return the
var_i name registered when their producing node was emitted.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns "0.0f" if inputs is null or index is out of range (safe constant).
Reads the input_edge at inputs[index], fetches the source node via
Edge.get_edge_source, then queries var_names Dict for the producing
node's name; returns the name on hit, "input_0[gid]" on miss (graph
inputs that have not been added to var_names).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - one List.get plus one Dict.get.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read on caller-owned data structures. Returns a borrowed String from
var_names (callers must not free).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_input_variable" that takes inputs as Integer, index as Integer, var_names as Integer returns String:
    If inputs is equal to 0:
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    If index is greater than or equal to proc length from List with inputs:
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    Let input_edge be proc get from List with inputs, index
    Let source_node be proc get_edge_source from Edge with input_edge

    Let var_name be proc get from Dict with var_names, source_node

    If var_name is equal to 0:
        Return "input_0[gid]"
    End If

    Return var_name
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits a commented stub showing how to call clGetDeviceInfo for the three
most useful device capabilities (max compute units, max work-group size,
local memory size). Commenting them out keeps the generated kernel header
portable while documenting the lookup signatures.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends six commented C lines that
declare local variables (cl_uint maxComputeUnits, size_t
maxWorkGroupSize, cl_ulong localMemSize) and the corresponding
clGetDeviceInfo calls with the right CL_DEVICE_* token constants. Returns
the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - a small fixed number of string appends.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation; output is commented C source that does not execute
unless the host project uncomments it.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_opencl_device_query" that takes nothing returns String:
    Let code be proc emitter_raw_create from Emitter

    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "// Query device capabilities:\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "// cl_uint maxComputeUnits;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_MAX_COMPUTE_UNITS, sizeof(maxComputeUnits , &maxComputeUnits, NULL);\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "// size_t maxWorkGroupSize;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_MAX_WORK_GROUP_SIZE, sizeof(maxWorkGroupSize , &maxWorkGroupSize, NULL);\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "// cl_ulong localMemSize;\n"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from Emitter with code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_LOCAL_MEM_SIZE, sizeof(localMemSize , &localMemSize, NULL);\n"

    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from Emitter with code
End Process
